text.i: Transportation Impact Assessment for the Via Moraga Project

page.text: This report presents the analysis and findings of the Transportation Impact Assessment (TIA) for the Via
Moraga subdivision (Project) located in Moraga, a town in Central Contra Costa County. This chapter
discusses the TIA purpose, analysis methods, criteria used to identify significant impacts, and report
The study’s purpose is to evaluate the transportation impacts of the Via Moraga subdivision. The Project
site is located within the Town of Moraga, adjacent to the cities of Orinda and Lafayette, as shown on
Figure 1. The proposed Project would construct 18 single-family detached homes on a vacant 1.95-acre
parcel with two new driveways on Moraga Road across from the Rheem Valley Shopping Center. A
conceptual project site plan is shown on Figure 2. As currently proposed, two full access driveways from
Moraga Road would provide unrestricted access to the loop roadway that would provide driveway access
This study addresses the Project’s impacts on the roadway system under two scenarios (Existing Plus
Project and Cumulative Plus Project) and discusses the adjacent bicycle, pedestrian, and transit network.
A site plan review was also conducted.
Project impacts to study area roadway facilities were determined by measuring the effect Project traffic
would have on intersections in the vicinity of the site during the morning (7:00 to 9:00 AM) and evening
(4:00 to 6:00 PM) peak periods. The following intersections, as shown on Figure 3, were selected based
on a review of the project location, and the amount of traffic that could be added to the intersections in
the vicinity of the site. The list of study locations was approved by Town staff.
